-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-27/copper-may-gain-as-strike-at-escondida-mine-goes-on-lme-preview.html
Copper, little changed in London
trading, may extend its biggest rally in almost three weeks on
speculation that a strike at  Chile ’s Escondida mine, the world’s
largest, could reduce global supplies.  Market News:  Metals News:  To contact the reporter on this story:
